President Donald J. Trump has directed United States Trade Representative Robert Lighthizer and Secretary of the Treasury Steven Mnuchin to travel to Beijing, China, for meetings starting on March 28, 2019. The purpose of these meetings is to continue negotiations with China in order to improve the trade relationship between the two countries. Deputy United States Trade Representative Jeffrey Gerrish and other senior officials will also be accompanying the principals. Additionally, a delegation from China led by Vice Premier Liu He will visit Washington for meetings starting on April 3, 2019.